# General Code Policy

## Code Quality
- Write clean code
- Follow SOLID principles
- Keep functions small
- Use meaningful names
- Add proper comments

## Naming Conventions
- Use descriptive names
- Follow language style
- Be consistent
- Avoid abbreviations
- Use proper casing

## Code Changes
- Make atomic changes
- Write clear commits
- Update documentation
- Add tests
- Review changes

## Code Structure
- Organize logically
- Keep files focused
- Use proper hierarchy
- Maintain modularity
- Follow patterns

## Best Practices
- Handle errors
- Write tests
- Document code
- Follow standards
- Use version control

## Security
- Validate input
- Handle secrets
- Update dependencies
- Follow guidelines
- Audit code

## Performance
- Optimize code (after initial implementation)
- Profile bottlenecks
- Cache effectively
- Use proper algorithms
- Monitor resources

## Documentation
- Write clear docs
- Keep docs updated
- Document APIs
- Add examples
- Explain complex logic

## Testing
- Write unit tests
- Write acceptance tests
- Add integration tests
- Test edge cases
- Mock dependencies
- Maintain coverage

## Maintenance
- Review regularly
- Update dependencies
- Fix technical debt
- Monitor issues
- CONTINUOUSLY improve code